        {
          "title": "A Quiet Place Part II",
          "year": 2021,
          "note": "A prequel-cold-open into a direct pickup from the first film's cliffhanger. More alien than the original, but Krasinski keeps the scale mostly contained to one family, plus Cillian Murphy's grieving survivor and a boat chase with a mute Scoot McNairy. The oxygen-canister math for the newborn is the whole podcast's real source of anxiety. Held to theaters exclusively for 45 days before Paramount+, a shorter window than Krasinski and Emily Blunt reportedly wanted."
        },
